 TER1/ter1-Bsi: Bsi-29 crossed with GG1935 ter1-Bcl/ter1-Acc:
Acc/Acc was transformed with pTER-Bcl resulting in a diploid stain with
three copies of TER1: ter1-Acc-URA3-ter1-Bcl on one chromosome and
ter1-Acc on the homologous chromosome, with capped telomeres. On
selection on 5-FOA, cells that retained one copy of ter1-Acc and one
copy of ter1-bcl were screened for by PCR and hybridization to a
Bcl–specific probe, as described for Acc-29 TER1/ter1-Bcl ex-Acc: spore
